<subSubSection id="C36DC1B0B05AFFF3FEAF51A8D593FD27" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BC8923BB05AFFF3FEAF51A8D50AFE70" blockId="19.[286,621,456,480]" box="[286,621,456,480]" pageId="19" pageNumber="147">
<heading id="D0802557B05AFFF3FEAF51A8D50AFE70" bold="true" box="[286,621,456,480]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" reason="2">
<emphasis id="B9034E29B05AFFF3FEAF51A8D50AFE70" bold="true" box="[286,621,456,480]" pageId="19" pageNumber="147">
<taxonomicName id="4C77E9B8B05AFFF3FEAF51A8D6A9FE70" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" box="[286,462,456,480]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicornis">
<emphasis id="B9034E29B05AFFF3FEAF51A8D6A9FE70" bold="true" box="[286,462,456,480]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="147">Achilia bicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC8923BB05AFFF3FF26519AD593FD27" blockId="19.[151,756,506,695]" pageId="19" pageNumber="147">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE6EFCAB05AFFF3FF26519AD615FD81" author="Jeannel R." box="[151,370,506,529]" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" pagination="295 - 479" refId="ref22040" refString="Jeannel R. 1962. Les Pselaphides de la Paleantarctide Occidentale [pp. 295 - 479]. In: Deboutteville C. D., E. Rapoport (eds), Biologie de l'Amerique Australe. Vol. I. Etude sur la Faune du Sol. Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique, Paris." type="book chapter" year="1962">Jeannel (1962: 398</bibRefCitation>
, 419) characterized this group as follows: elytra with 3 basal foveae; basal striae of first abdominal tergite separated about by a quarter of the tergal width; male frons with two occipital pubescent lobes protruding and separated by a large median furrow with a small median vertexal apophysis; frons anteriorly
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36DC1B0B05AFFF3FC8E5162D332FD95" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC8923BB05AFFF3FC8E5162D333FEAB" blockId="19.[831,1437,258,517]" pageId="19" pageNumber="147">largely depressed as a smooth transverse groove; dorsal struts of aedeagus simple.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC8923BB05AFFF3FC8E5125D332FD95" blockId="19.[831,1437,258,517]" pageId="19" pageNumber="147">
This group includes 
<taxonomicName id="4C77E9B8B05AFFF3FB895125D202FECC" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" box="[1080,1381,325,348]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicornis">
<emphasis id="B9034E29B05AFFF3FB895125D3D0FECC" box="[1080,1207,325,348]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="147">A. bicornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE6EFCAB05AFFF3FB795125D202FECC" author="Jeannel R." box="[1224,1381,325,348]" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" pagination="295 - 479" refId="ref22040" refString="Jeannel R. 1962. Les Pselaphides de la Paleantarctide Occidentale [pp. 295 - 479]. In: Deboutteville C. D., E. Rapoport (eds), Biologie de l'Amerique Australe. Vol. I. Etude sur la Faune du Sol. Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique, Paris." type="book chapter" year="1962">Jeannel, 1962</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C77E9B8B05AFFF3FC8E5107D30BFEEE" authority="Newton, 2017" authorityName="Newton" authorityYear="2017" box="[831,1132,359,382]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilotides">
<emphasis id="B9034E29B05AFFF3FC8E5107D4A0FEEE" box="[831,967,359,382]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="147">A. chilotides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE6EFCAB05AFFF3FC615107D30BFEEE" author="Newton A. F." box="[976,1132,359,382]" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" pagination="1 - 52" refId="ref22290" refString="Newton A. F. 2017. Nomenclatural and taxonomic changes in Staphyliniformia (Coleoptera). Insecta Mundi, 0595: 1 - 52." type="book chapter" year="2017">Newton, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Howewer, our study of the 
<typeStatus id="54CC2C99B05AFFF3FC8E51E9D40AFE30" box="[831,877,393,416]" pageId="19" pageNumber="147">type</typeStatus>
materials revealed that 
<taxonomicName id="4C77E9B8B05AFFF3FBC551E9D2FBFE30" authority="Newton, 2017" authorityName="Newton" authorityYear="2017" box="[1140,1436,393,416]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilotides">
<emphasis id="B9034E29B05AFFF3FBC551E9D39CFE30" box="[1140,1275,393,416]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="147">A. chilotides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE6EFCAB05AFFF3FAB251E9D2FBFE30" author="Newton A. F." box="[1283,1436,393,416]" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" pagination="1 - 52" refId="ref22290" refString="Newton A. F. 2017. Nomenclatural and taxonomic changes in Staphyliniformia (Coleoptera). Insecta Mundi, 0595: 1 - 52." type="book chapter" year="2017">Newton, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C77E9B8B05AFFF3FBE851CAD2FEFE51" authority="(Schaufuss, 1880)" baseAuthorityName="Schaufuss" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1113,1433,426,449]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excisa">
<emphasis id="B9034E29B05AFFF3FBE851CAD3A6FE51" box="[1113,1217,426,449]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="147">A. excisa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE6EFCAB05AFFF3FB6451CAD2F6FE51" author="Schaufuss L. W." box="[1237,1425,426,449]" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" pagination="481 - 511" refId="ref22671" refString="Schaufuss L. W. 1880 (1879). Beschreibung sechzig neuer Pselaphiden. Nunquam Otiosus 3: 481 - 511." type="journal article" year="1880">Schaufuss, 1880</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Consequently the 
<taxonomicName id="4C77E9B8B05AFFF3FBA151ACD3EBFE73" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" box="[1040,1164,460,483]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicornis">
<emphasis id="B9034E29B05AFFF3FBA151ACD3EBFE73" box="[1040,1164,460,483]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="147">A. bicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group now only holds 
<taxonomicName id="4C77E9B8B05AFFF3FC8E518ED335FD95" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" box="[831,1106,494,517]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicornis">
<emphasis id="B9034E29B05AFFF3FC8E518ED4D3FD95" box="[831,948,494,517]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="147">A. bicornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE6EFCAB05AFFF3FC0A518ED335FD95" author="Jeannel R." box="[955,1106,494,517]" pageId="19" pageNumber="147" pagination="295 - 479" refId="ref22040" refString="Jeannel R. 1962. Les Pselaphides de la Paleantarctide Occidentale [pp. 295 - 479]. In: Deboutteville C. D., E. Rapoport (eds), Biologie de l'Amerique Australe. Vol. I. Etude sur la Faune du Sol. Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique, Paris." type="book chapter" year="1962">Jeannel, 1962</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
